==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rother
<hw>Roth"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>hry⟦edh⟧er</ets>; cf. D. <ets>rund</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Bovine.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A bovine
beast.</def></def2> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rother beasts</b></col>, <cd>cattle of the bovine genus;
black cattle.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>Golding.</au> --
<col><b>Rother soil</b></col>, <cd>the dung of rother
beasts.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rother</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rother
<hw>Roth"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. See <er>Rudder</er>.]</ety>
<def>A rudder.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Rother nail</b></col>, <cd>a nail with a very full head,
used for fastening the rudder irons of ships; -- so called by
shipwrights.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rotifer</ent>⟦br⟧
